steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"rfg5","text":"Grow MEFs to 90-95% confluency in 15-cm cell culture dish","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"58l21","text":"Aspirate the medium and add 15 ml of Mitomycin C solution to cover the surface","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4vnpt","text":"Aspirate Mitomycin C solution from the plates and wash 4 times with DPBS (with Ca/Mg) and final wash with DPBS (w/o Ca/Mg).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"b1ebn","text":"Add Trypsin and incubate in 37°C; 5% CO2 for   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":45,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"bel5e","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"duration","mutability":"","data":{"duration":300,"guid":"E85C44107D9611ECB0AEC528C800364D","id":0,"label":"","pause":null,"preset":[],"start":null}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"f5u6s","text":"Add MEF medium to neutralize the Trypsin and collect the solution into a conical tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"9rtvn","text":"Discard supernatant and re-suspend the cells in fresh MEF medium","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"v0ql","text":"Mitomycin C treated cells can be either freshly plated as feeder cells for hPCS cultures or frozen as Mitomycin C inactivated stocks at 10x106 cells/vial. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":141,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6q029","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6nbk0","text":"A protocol on freezing MEFs can be found in the collection \"Maintenance and inactivation of mouse embryonic fibroblasts (MEFs) as feeder cells for human pluripotent stem cell culture.\" A link to this collection can be found in the title section of this protocol, located above","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
